The Google fact evaluation data asks the rater to judge whether
a candidate "fact" is correct or not, with an option to skip
if the rater is unsure. The possible answers are:

Categories
0       No - incorrect
1       Yes -  correct
2       Skip - unsure

The CSV basic data format is quite simple; the first line names 
the columns, and we see below the first 9 judgments in the file:
